{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> θηρίον</b>, τό <br /> (in form <i>diminutive</i> of θήρ), <b>wild animal</b>, especially of such as are hunted, μάλα γὰρ μέγα θηρίον ἦεν, of a stag, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 10.171, 180 (never in 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad”)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; in Trag. only in Satyric drama, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ichn.” 147 (uncertain in 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Fragmenta - American Journal of Philology” 26): used in Prose for θήρ, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 1.2.7, 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 12.163, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of the spider's <b>prey</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 623a27 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; frequently of elephants, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 11.1.12, +others\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]: <i>plural</i>, <b>beasts</b>, opposed to men, birds, and fishes, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “hymnus ad Venerem” 4, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.108. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> generally, <b>animal</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 1.119; νενόμισται πῦρ θ. εἶναι ἔμψυχον [prev. author] 3.16 \">Refs</a>]; of men, ἄνθρωπος πάντων θ. θεειδέστατον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Antipho Sophista 48; εἰς θηρίου βίον ἀφικνεῖσθαι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 249b; also θ. ὕειον [prev. author] “R.” 535e \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of the dog, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 25.79 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; of fishes, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 598b1 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; of eels, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Antiphanes Comicus 147.7 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; of leeches, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 4.951.101 (Epid.) \">Refs</a>]; of other small creatures, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 552b11, 625b32, 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus cited in 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 19.103, 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 19.6; οὐκ ἔστιν οὐδὲν θ. τῶν ἰχθύων ἀτυχέστερον 4th c.BC: Antiphanes Comicus 161.1; opposed to plants, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 188b: proverbial, ἢ θηρίον ἢ θεός\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], either above or below the nature of man, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1253a29, compare “EN” 1145a25. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>beast</b>, especially as hostile and odious to man, θηρία τε καὶ βοτά <b>carnivora</b> and graminivora, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Menexenus” 237d \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>monster, creature</b>, of sharks, etc., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.44 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of Typhon, etc., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 230a, “R.” 588e \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of the Satyrs, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ichn.” [same place] \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ταυτὶ ποδαπὰ τὰ θ.; [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 184, compare “Av.” 93. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__3.b</b></Level4> <b>poisonous animal</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Dioscorides (Dioscurides) Medicus 1.75, NT.Act.28.4. \">NT+1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> in Medicine texts,= θηρίωμα, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “Κωακαὶ προγνώσιες” 459, “Loc.Hom.” 29, compare 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus [prev. cited] \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> as a term of reproach, <b>beast, creature</b>, ὦ δειλότατον σὺ θηρίον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 439, compare “Eq.” 273; κόλακι, δεινῷ θηρίῳ 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 240b; Κρῆτες, κακὰ θ. 6th c.BC: Epimenides Philosophus 1 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; δυσνουθέτητον θ., of poverty, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus “Γεωργός” 78; ἡ μουσικὴ ἀεί τι καινὸν θηρίον τίκτει 4th c.BC: Anaxilas Comicus 27, compare 5th c.BC: Eupolis Comicus 132 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τί δέ, εἰ αὐτοῦ τοῦ θηρίου ἠκούσατ; said by Aeschines of Demosthenes, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Plinius Rerum Naturalium Scriptor “Ep.” 2.3.10\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; θ. συνεστιώμενον, of woman, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Secundus Gnomologus “Sententiae - FPG” 8. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> Astron., the constellation [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Lupus”, 4th c.BC: Eudoxus Astronomus cited in 2nd c.BC: Hipparchus Astronomicus 1.2.20, Vett. Val. 6.13. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G2342","accentedUnicode":"θηρίον","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G2339","matchingForm":"θήρα","stepTransliteration":"thēra","gloss":"trap","_zh_tw_Gloss":"陷阱","_es_Gloss":"trampa","_zh_Gloss":"陷阱"},{"strongNumber":"G2341","matchingForm":"θηριομαχέω","stepTransliteration":"thēriomacheō","gloss":"to fight beasts","_zh_tw_Gloss":"曾同野獸戰鬥","_es_Gloss":"luchar contra fieras","_zh_Gloss":"曾同野兽战斗"}],"shortDef":"(wild) animal, (fiendish) beast, snake","mediumDef":"(wild) animal, (fiendish) beast, snake <br /><b>a beast, wild animal,</b> <ref='Mrk.1.13'>Mk. 1:13</ref>; <ref='Act.10.12'>Acts 10:12;</ref> <i>metaphorically</i> <b>a brute, brutish man,</b> <ref='Tit.1.12'>Tit. 1:12</ref>","stepGloss":"wild animal","stepTransliteration":"thērion","count":47,"_es_Definition":"animal, bestia ; animal salvaje ; serpiente (HCH.28:4,5)","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 動物, 野獸<br> a) 真實的<br> b) 超自然界的<br>2) (邪惡的人) 野獸 (多 1:12)","_zh_Definition":"1) 动物, 野兽<br> a) 真实的<br> b) 超自然界的<br>2) (邪恶的人) 野兽 (多 1:12)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"con thú rừng; con thú dữ. ẩn dụ một kẻ vũ phu, một người đàn ông thú tính.","_zh_tw_Gloss":"獸","_es_Gloss":"animal salvaje","_zh_Gloss":"兽"}]}